      </p>

      <h2>2. Don't be afraid of playing with lengths</h2>
      <p>
        A variation in the length of chains is the key to an effortlessly chic-looking layered chain look.
        To make it easier for you to choose the right lengths, here is an example:
      </p>

        <p>• 16-inch chain for a choker</p>
        <p>• 18-inch chain for the mid chain</p>
        <p>• 20 or 22-inch chain as the last chain with a pendant that describes your personality the best
        </p>

      <p>
        The pendant creates a natural drop and prevents the chains from looking heavy or getting tangled amongst themselves.
        The drop also draws the eye towards the center of the chest, giving the neckline a graceful look.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Mix metals and textures!</h2>
      <p>
        Now you know that creating the perfect visual interest is the key to a great layered look.
        Now, to create a good visual interest, you can do a lot of different things.
        Combining textures and mixing metals can be your new best friend!
      </p>

      <p>
        Textural contrast lets each chain stand out without overpowering the others.
        Mixing silver with rose gold or gold-plated chains adds character to your ensemble.
      </p>

      <h2>4. A pendant goes a long way</h2>
      <p>
        A good pendant is more than an accessory; it can not only give away your essence long before you break that ice,
        but also become the reason you are remembered long after you exit a conversation.
      </p>

      <p>
        A well-chosen pendant holds the power to anchor your entire look, and keeping it on the longest chain creates an
        elegant drop that naturally elongates the entire look, bringing the ease that is essential for that effortlessly chic look.
      </p>

